<item>
            <title>[TIKA-274] CharsetDetector.setDeclaredEncoding has no effect</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-274</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In TXTParser.java we may read:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;        // Use the declared character encoding, if available&lt;br/&gt;
        String encoding = metadata.get(Metadata.CONTENT_ENCODING);&lt;br/&gt;
        if (encoding != null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
            detector.setDeclaredEncoding(encoding);
        }

&lt;p&gt;But it seems to be not implemented feature.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
